messages.message:
@Atinder @Gaurav Saini can you update on the status here?
I see it still doesn’t work for me at uat if I have the e-mail setting turned on.

@Sławek Biel that is fine. We are not going to fix these cases in 24.36. The feature isn't meant for external release yet and was only enabled for users with instabase email id (it was enabled by default for instabase users, we have now made it opt-in to avoid confusion).
Ok, so it’s off for Instabase employees by default now? In that case I guess it’s fine, I’ll mark the test as passing.
Yep, now it's off by default for IB users.
